-- Singapore Q3 private home prices drop 0.7 pct q/q, extend falls
-- By Masayuki Kitano
-- Thu Oct 23, 2014 08:43PM EDT
-- None



SINGAPORE, Oct 24 (Reuters) - Singapore's Urban Redevelopment Authority released detailed estimates for the change in private home prices in the third  quarter of 2014:

Quarter-on-quarter, percentage price change:  Quarter  Q3/2014  Q2/2014  Singapore -0.7 -1.0  private home prices  CONTEXT: - Private residential property prices fell 0.7 percent in the third quarter, declining for the fourth consecutive quarter. - Prices dropped across all segments of the residential property market.   - Prices of non-landed properties in the core central region  fell 0.8 percent, after slipping 1.5 percent in the previous quarter. Prices outside the central region dropped 0.3 percent after falling 0.9 percent in the previous quarter.